@Icheerleadforputs As I said in another post, $ETSY would need to reach a share price of $200 before they were even as expensive as $MSFT by most metrics, and that accounts for both trailing and forward growth. Given the current market conditions they&#39;re dirt cheap. I would be more of a &quot;hold&quot; if we weren&#39;t in Dot-Com Bubble 2.0, and it really just depends on how long that can continue to sustain itself. 

When the bubble does pop (see below for just how little this &quot;correction&quot; has actually done) then *every* company, including those that are fairly valued, will be hit and hit hard. However, it&#39;s the real bubbles like $TSLA $SHOP $SNOW that will take years to recover, if ever, as Amazon took a decade to after Dot-Com Bubble 1.0. 

Etsy will be fine, it&#39;s trading at a fair value premium, but not so much that it won&#39;t have a far faster recovery when this bubble of epic proportions finally comes back to reality.
